com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2.util

Class PropagatorFunctionSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2.util.PropagatorFunctionSource
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PropagatorFunctionSourceBindings

    public abstract class PropagatorFunctionSource
extends java.lang.Object
    The base class for implementing the inbound bindings for one PropagatorFunction on one EObject.

    Following features must be supported by a PropagatorFunctionSource

    • associated with one PropagatorFunction: the one that is binding
    • associated with one EObject: the object bound to the PropagatorFunction
    • listening to changes in the EObject and forwarding touch() to the PropagatorFunction
    • collecting the antecedents of the PropagatorFunction
    • managing the dependencies

      • initDependencies

        public void initDependencies()
        The method initializes the dependencies this PropagatorFunctionSource.

        This will happen when the source is added to the adapter by PropagatorFunctionAdapter.addSource(PropagatorFunctionSource)

        Sources are either primary sources or dependent sources. The former are created by PropagatorFunction.enable(), while the latter are created when some relations is set, so in the touch(EObject)
